author: Karlee Weinmann
title: Manufacturers provide springboard for Minnesota
text:
Home / News / Business & Economy / Manufacturers provide springboard for Minnesota U.S. factories were a little less busy in July. The Institute of Purchasing Managers’ manufacturing index slipped to 52.7 last month from 53.5 in June. Any reading above 50 indicates growth. The index had risen in May and June. Factories’ exports are contracting, partly because a strong dollar makes U.S. goods more expensive. In this June 22 photo, a Buick Verano is assembled at General Motors’ plant in Orion Township, Michigan. (AP PHOTO) Manufacturers provide springboard for Minnesota By: Karlee Weinmann August 3, 2015 1:38 pm 0 Propped up again by a strong showing by manufacturers, Minnesota’s growth prospects outpaced other Midwestern states in July, according to a Monday report.
